transcript: No one ever offers me drugs on the street. I don’t know what it is about me that screams “SAY NO TO DRUGS,” but apparently something does. It’s not a very cool feeling. I’m not saying I need to have drugs, but being offered is something to be desired. I even asked my interns once how they get drugs, but I don’t think their advice was applicable to me. “Do you party” sounds more like I’m asking someone to an orgy, and I have stereotypes about orgy people. Anyway, I had a moment of glory a few months ago. I was walking home, and a kid walked up behind me, and asked whether I wanted to buy some weed. I wanted to hug him, but I thought that would be inappropriate. So I bought his weed and promptly lost it at home.
